task.en: I am developing an app, but it seems the logo is above the text. How to modify the code to put the logo below the text without modifying the attributes of everything? Please help me do it.

pre_command: osascript -e 'tell application "Xcode" to close windows' && rm -rf /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp && cp -r /Users/ec2-user/Benchmark_Backup/BenchmarkApp /Users/ec2-user/Documents && cd /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp && git checkout 5ba51e8 && open -a Xcode /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp
grading_command: cat /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp/BenchmarkApp/ContentView.swift | sed -e 's|//.*||' -e 's|/\*[^*]*\*+\([^/]*\*/\)| |g' -e 's|/\*.*||' -e 's|.*\*/||' | tr -d '\n' | tr -d ' ' | grep -q 'structContentView:View{varbody:someView{VStack{Text("Hello,world!")Image(systemName:"globe").imageScale(.large).foregroundStyle(.tint)}.padding()}}' && echo "True" || echo "False"
